sql:
SELECT total_capacity, predicted_demand
FROM station_bike_availability
WHERE bike_type_id = 0 AND station_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "winds of demand are strong" refers to a high predicted demand for bikes at the station;
- "sails of availability are not yet full" refers to the availability percentage of bikes being less than 100%;
- "at least one bike available" means the available quantity of bikes is greater than 0;
- "forecasted demand is more than 3" means the predicted demand is greater than 3.
